title: Kate Middleton to join Prince William on her first State banquet to welcome China’s president
text:
Tweet 
Although it hasn’t been confirmed yet, the Duchess of Cambridge, née Kate Middleton, is said to be getting ready for her first State banquet later this month. 
The State banquet, which will be held at Buckingham Palace when China’s president Xi Jinping and his wife Peng Liyuan will come to the UK, and is set to be hosted by Queen Elizabeth II. 
And according to a royal source, cited by Daily Mail , “Catherine will be there.” 
“The State visit is a result of the invitation that William made when he visited China earlier this year.” 
Information regarding Duchess Kate’s participation at her first State banquet emerged in August. Given the protocol of the event, Kate is likely to wear a tiara at the banquet. 
The Duke of Cambridge was welcomed by president Xi Jinping in China back in March. 
Kate will definitely also look ravishing in an elegant gown at the world premiere of the latest James Bond movie, on Oct 26, where she will be accompanied by her husband Prince William and her brother-in-law Prince Harry. Spread the rumor
